parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Dim or inadequate backup lights can reduce visibility when reversing, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries, especially in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Backup lights appear dim or weak
difficulty seeing obstacles or pedestrians when reversing
reduced visibility when reversing in low-light conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle sticking and unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The throttle pedal sticks when removing foot from the accelerator pedal
the truck continues to accelerate even after removing foot from the pedal
the engine RPM increases unexpectedly
the vehicle surges forward without driver input
difficulty controlling the vehicle's speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the steering system can cause the vehicle to wander or drift, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the steering wheel feels loose or unstable
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive travel of the ABS brake pedal can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels further than usual when stopping
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal has a delayed response to braking input
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of Goodyear tires can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Tire blowouts
tire tread separation
uneven tire wear
vibration while driving
loss of air pressure
tire noise
and difficulty maintaining vehicle control.
